</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[409,493,818,839]" pageId="3" pageNumber="172" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[162,777,909,1054]" box="[162,278,909,930]" pageId="3" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis box="[162,278,909,930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="172">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[162,777,909,1054]" pageId="3" pageNumber="172">
The genus is named after the late Mónica Montú (Universidade Federal do 
<collectingRegion box="[404,614,971,993]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="3" pageNumber="172">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[625,695,971,993]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="172">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) and is combined with the termination 
<emphasis box="[520,578,1001,1022]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="172">karis</emphasis>
, derived from the Greek name for shrimp. Gender feminine.
</paragraph>
